What is the Youth Innovation Portal?

The Youth Innovation Portal is a platform for innovators to showcase projects, request funding and certificates, register for events, and collaborate with peers and mentors in Ethiopia.

How do I become an innovator?

Create an account, complete your profile with accurate information, submit a verification request with required documents, and wait for admin approval. Once verified, you can access all features.

How can I post a project?

After logging in, go to Projects and click Create Project. Provide a clear title, description, category, goals, timeline, and any media. Submit for review if required by admins.

Can I edit or delete my project?

Yes. Open your project detail page and use Edit to update fields or Delete to remove it. Some fields may be locked after approval; contact support if needed.

How do I request funding?

Open Requests → Funding Request. Fill out your project details, budget, and justification. Submit and track status in your dashboard. You’ll receive notifications when admins respond.

How do I request a certificate?

Go to Requests → Certificate Request. Provide the necessary information and submit. You can track the request status and download the certificate once approved.

How do I register for events?

Open Events, select an event, and click Register. Your registration appears under Applications or your profile. You’ll be notified about updates and schedules.

I forgot my password. What should I do?

On the Login page, click Forgot password? Enter your email to receive a secure reset link. Follow the link to set a new password. Links expire in 1 hour for security.

How does profile verification work?

Submit a verification application with required documents. Admins review and may request more info. You’ll see status updates and get a notification when approved or rejected.
